---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { getSessionUser } from '../lib/auth';

export const prerender = false;

const myPrizeAffiliateUrl = 'https://myprize.us/invite/goobspins';
const user = await getSessionUser(Astro.request);
---

<BaseLayout title="Getting Started | SweepsIntel" user={user} currentPath={Astro.url.pathname}>
  <div class="page-shell page-stack">
    <article class="guide-body">
      <h1>How to Start Earning with Sweepstakes Casinos</h1>

      <section>
        <h2>1. What sweepstakes casinos are</h2>
        <p>
          Sweepstakes casinos are online gaming platforms that use a dual-currency model. You play with Gold Coins for fun, and
          Sweeps Coins are the redeemable currency that can be exchanged for real money where the model is allowed.
        </p>
        <p>
          They operate under sweepstakes rules rather than traditional real-money casino licensing. That means the purchase is for
          entertainment currency, while redeemable currency is framed as a promotional bonus and must also be available through a
          no-purchase path.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>2. Understanding SC and GC</h2>
        <p>
          SC stands for Sweeps Coins. That is the redeemable balance you care about. GC stands for Gold Coins. That is the
          play-for-fun balance you receive when you buy packages.
        </p>
        <p>
          Example: you buy 200K GC for $9.99 and receive 20 free SC as the bonus. The GC is entertainment currency. The SC is what
          you play through and eventually redeem.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>3. Your first day at MyPrize</h2>
        <div class="screenshot-placeholder">[SCREENSHOT: MyPrize signup page]</div>
        <p><strong>3a.</strong> Sign up at MyPrize using the link below.</p>
        <p><strong>3b.</strong> Complete ID verification. Do not skip this. It is one of the easiest ways to delay your first redemption.</p>
        <div class="screenshot-placeholder">[SCREENSHOT: ID verification screen]</div>
        <p><strong>3c.</strong> Purchase the first welcome offer. Start with the smallest offer first so you learn the mechanics without overcommitting.</p>
        <div class="screenshot-placeholder">[SCREENSHOT: Welcome offer purchase screen]</div>
        <p>
          MyPrize uses batched playthrough. Each purchase can have its own separate progress tracker. That looks more complicated
          than it is. You just need to finish the active batch before redeeming.
        </p>
        <p><strong>3d.</strong> Open <code>TODO: wash game recommendation</code> and play at <code>TODO: bet size</code> per spin.</p>
        <div class="screenshot-placeholder">[SCREENSHOT: Game play screen]</div>
        <p>
          The goal here is simple: meet the 1x playthrough requirement on your SC as efficiently as possible. You are not trying to
          force action. You are just completing the required loop cleanly.
        </p>
        <p><strong>3e.</strong> Check your Playthrough screen, find the active batch, and keep playing until that batch reaches 100%.</p>
        <div class="screenshot-placeholder">[SCREENSHOT: Playthrough tracker screen]</div>
        <p><strong>3f.</strong> Submit your first redemption.</p>
        <div class="screenshot-placeholder">[SCREENSHOT: Redemption submission screen]</div>
        <p><strong>3g.</strong> Wait for payment. MyPrize offers instant or same-day processing in many cases.</p>
        <div class="screenshot-placeholder">[SCREENSHOT: Money received confirmation]</div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>4. Key terms defined</h2>
        <p><strong>Playthrough:</strong> how many times you need to wager your SC before you can redeem it.</p>
        <p><strong>Wash / wash game:</strong> a low-volatility game you use mainly to satisfy playthrough efficiently.</p>
        <p><strong>SC-to-USD ratio:</strong> how many Sweeps Coins equal one dollar. A 1:1 ratio means 1 SC equals $1.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>5. Common new player mistakes</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Do not skip ID verification.</li>
          <li>Do not try to redeem before playthrough completes.</li>
          <li>Do not chase losses. Set a daily limit and learn the mechanics first.</li>
          <li>Start with the smallest welcome offer so the process is easy to understand.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>6. What&apos;s next</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Add more casinos to your tracker.</li>
          <li>Check daily for reset timers so you never miss a bonus.</li>
          <li>Watch the community intel feed for flash deals and promo codes.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="affiliate-cta">
        <h2>Ready to start?</h2>
        <p>Use code: <strong>goobspins</strong></p>
        <a
          href={myPrizeAffiliateUrl}
          id="getting-started-affiliate"
          data-fallback-url={myPrizeAffiliateUrl}
          class="cta-button"
        >
          Sign up at MyPrize -&gt;
        </a>
      </section>
    </article>
  </div>

  <script is:inline>
    const cta = document.getElementById('getting-started-affiliate');
    if (cta) {
      cta.addEventListener('click', async (event) => {
        event.preventDefault();
        const fallbackUrl = cta.getAttribute('data-fallback-url');
        try {
          const controller = new AbortController();
          const timeout = window.setTimeout(() => controller.abort(), 3000);
          const response = await fetch('/api/affiliate/click', {
            method: 'POST',
            headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
            body: JSON.stringify({ casino_slug: 'myprize', referrer_source: 'getting_started' }),
            signal: controller.signal,
          });
          window.clearTimeout(timeout);
          const data = await response.json();
          window.open(data.url || fallbackUrl, '_blank', 'noopener,noreferrer');
        } catch (error) {
          console.error(error);
          if (fallbackUrl) {
            window.open(fallbackUrl, '_blank', 'noopener,noreferrer');
          }
        }
      });
    }
  </script>

  <style>
    .guide-body {
      max-width: 720px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      display: grid;
      gap: 2rem;
      line-height: 1.8;
    }

    .guide-body h1,
    .guide-body h2,
    .guide-body p,
    .guide-body ul {
      margin: 0;
    }

    .guide-body section {
      display: grid;
      gap: 1rem;
    }

    .guide-body ul {
      padding-left: 1.2rem;
    }

    .screenshot-placeholder {
      min-height: 180px;
      border: 1px dashed var(--color-border);
      border-radius: 1rem;
      background: var(--bg-secondary);
      display: grid;
      place-items: center;
      color: var(--color-muted);
      text-align: center;
      padding: 1rem;
    }

    .affiliate-cta {
      padding: 1.5rem;
      border-radius: 1.5rem;
      border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.12), var(--bg-secondary));
    }

    .cta-button {
      display: inline-flex;
      width: fit-content;
      padding: 0.95rem 1.2rem;
      border-radius: 999px;
      background: var(--color-primary);
      color: var(--text-primary);
      text-decoration: none;
      font-weight: 700;
    }
  </style>
</BaseLayout>

